Look at that, breakfast of champions! Shoutout to our wholesale partners over at @cafecomodo, who not only do a fantastic job with their food and drinks menu, but they also serve our coffee. Go check them out! 🤙
.
Photo by @enjoyamsterdamwithme

#Lot61family
•
If you’re a regular or frequent customer, you most probably know Alice. With her hard work and bubbly personality, we’re grateful having her as part of our team. Originally from Norwich, the UK, she is a very talented barista, a passionate graphic designer and a big dog lover!

For the bagels aficionados (such as ourselves) in Amsterdam, there’s now a proper hot spot in the city! We’re thrilled to welcome @flos_appetizing to the neighborhood and equally excited to have our Nosegrind blend alongside their finger lickin’ menu. Bagels, schmears, smoked fish and fresh toppings, plus sweet breads and cookies. Do we need to go on?
🥯🥯🥯
Go check it out and show them some love!
Good morning & Happy Valentines dears! Grab your loved one and come hang out for a cup of coffee. Or two. Have a lovely day! ☕️ ❤️

Good morning! We’re pumped to get this delish Guatemala back on the grinder as our February special. Expect fruity notes of raspberry and all around chocolate sweetness. Come in and ask our baristas 😎🤙

Good morning! Cheeky throwback to a recent exciting event! We were super delighted to be part of @gant presentation on its new sustainable collection at @thewhitedoorstudio. We suggested to brew our Burundi Gahahe on Chemex matching the flavors of the breakfast created by @elise_henry_creations. Thanks for having us! 🙌

It’s that time of the month, guys! We’re thrilled to introduce our filter special for the month of February • naturally processed Myanmar from Ho Hwayt village.
•
Expect this coffee to be winey and sweet, with notes of dried fruits and cocoa nibs in the finish. Available every day on batch brew and on our retail shelf 🤙

Did you know that in addition to our flagship cafe on Kinkerstraat we also have a pop-up espresso bar in the trendy Urban Outfitters store, right by Dam Square? Next time you’re in the area, consider dropping by. Our baristas Nathan, Tay, Rosa or Jill will welcome you with a big smile and a delicious cup of coffee. And yes, we also have retail coffee bags too 😉

Good morning! Did you know that in our shop, alongside our Fivr 1kg, we also have large bags of your favorite blends, Bombora and Zimzala? If it’s for the office machine, a large family or you just can’t get enough of our delicious coffee, we got you covered! 👍

Have a great weekend and see you soon!

Before opening our doors to you each morning, we will spend as much as it’s needed to ensure the espresso is “dialed in” and tastes delicious. Using dose and grind size, we work on a recipe which will produce an ideal balance between sweetness and acidity, a great mouth feel and a long pleasant aftertaste 👌

We love our customers. Some come in for a meeting, some to enjoy an early coffee on their way to work, some bring their friends and family to share the moment. We’re delighted to roast, brew and serve our best coffees! Thanks for coming along and being part of our journey 🙏

Good morning! Keep the cold away with a freshly brewed mug of our month’s filter special.
•
In January we’re excited to have sourced and roasted a delicious Kenyan coffee which we’re offering as a filter. It’s full bodied, honey sweet and reminds us slightly of melon and passion fruit. You’ll find it on our batch throughout the month. Also, don’t be shy, have a look at our retail shelf and grab a bag for home as well. Limited stock available 😉

Boom! 💥 Throughout the month of January we are serving this special single origin espresso from Uganda! It’s full bodied, smooth and juicy. It has notes of blueberries & lots of chocolate sweetness. We love it straight as espresso, but tastes magnificent too in combination with milk 👌
• 
The coffee, of SL-28 and SL-34 varieties, grows at 1,800 meters and has been naturally processed.
Good morning! Croissants are baking and espresso is being dialed in. We expect a crisp yet sunny Saturday here in Amsterdam. We look forward welcoming you in our cafe, see you soon!
Another beautiful and chilly morning in the city of Amsterdam. As usual, we will keep you warm with delicious freshly brewed coffee and good vibes 🤙

Good morning!
•
Balancing equal parts espresso and silky steamed milk, we love serving our cortados in these beautiful glasses from @notneutral 🤙
Goedemorgen! There’s almost nothing we like more than the smell of freshly ground coffee. Have a great week! 🤙

Our regulars are cooler than yours! 😜
.
We’re super grateful to be surrounded by an amazing community of people. Many of them are not just customers, but we’ve grown together along the years and we’re fortunate to call them our friends 🙏

Showing some respect for our much beloved Zimzala house blend!
.
Balancing Brazil and Peru in equal parts, this blend is nutty, chocolaty and pleasantly acidic, making it a winner for any day. Always available in our cafe! 🤙

Good morning & Happy New Year! We love making coffee for the city which loves drinking it.
.
Today we open at 10 am. Let’s start the year right with freshly brewed coffee & all around good vibes. See you soon!
We wish you a happy & well caffeinated 2020! Lots of love from the Lot61 team  XXX

Last coffee of the decade guys, what’s it gonna be? 😏 Today we have normal opening hours. Drop by for a cup of coffee before we wrap up this year!
.
Check our stories too & pick your favorite coffees of 2019. Two lucky winners will get a bag of coffee from us. Good luck! 🍀
Good morning! Going at it again. We expect a beautiful day outside and a full house inside 🤙 What are you up to this weekend?
Good morning & Merry Christmas! Today we have normal opening hours. Come on over for some jolly vibes & a delicious cup of coffee! 🎄
Tomorrow our cafe is closed, but tonight we will make sure to leave out a glass of milk and a plate of our legendary chocolate chip cookies 🎅 🍪 🥛
